sions for common objects and experiences. A Maya-English-Spanish glossary with extensive usage examples and an English-Maya glossary conclude the book. Note: The supplemental audiocasette, Spoken Maya for Travelers and Students, is now available as a free download.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aMaya languagevConversation and phrase booksxEnglish. 0aMayasxSocial life and customs. 0aYucatan Peninsula--Description and travel. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Native American Languages.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/70838940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292759572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292759572/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK